6-thioguanine triphosphate, a metabolite of azathioprine, modulates activation of rac1 when costimulated with CD28, inducing T cell apoptosis.[A19872] This may be mediated through rac1''s action on mitogen-activated protein kinase, NF-kappaB.[A19872]', 'Azathioprine is an immunosuppressive agent which functions through modulation of rac1 to induce T cell apoptosis, as well as other unknown immunosuppressive functions.[A19872] It has a long duration of action as it is given daily, and has a narrow therapeutic index.[L11214] Patients should be counselled regarding the risk of malignancies of the skin and lymphomas.[L11214]', 'DrugBank', 0, 0, 0);
